INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('497','1','2015-12-16 17:37:47','2015-12-16 17:37:47','<strong>What specification do the courses follow?</strong>\r\n\r\nBoth courses were produced following the international GCSE specifications which are recognised by education establishments all around the world.\r\n\r\n<strong>What format do the videos take?</strong>\r\n\r\nEvery video consists of up to 100 detailed Powerpoint slides that provide clear and concise instruction. I have included my own narration over all of the slides, so it’s just like having your own personal teacher sat by your side.\r\n\r\n<strong>What devices can I watch the videos on?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe videos are in .mp4 format so they can be watched on most devices, such as: PC\'s, laptops, tablets, iPad\'s etc.\r\n\r\nOnce downloaded you can put the videos on a device that isn\'t connected to the internet, stopping you or your child from being distracted! :)\r\n\r\n<strong>If I watch all of the videos will I have sufficient knowledge to pass GCSE exams in the subjects?</strong>\r\n\r\nYes – I have covered everything required by the specification. However, you should really not rely on just one source for your information, especially if you’re going for the higher grades. I always recommend to my students that they have at least one other source of information, such as a relevant textbook. You also need to check out the exam board specifications.\r\n\r\n<strong>I live in the USA, so I don’t understand all this \'GCSE\' stuff – what age group are these videos aimed at?</strong>\r\n\r\nGCSE exams are internationally recognised qualifications and are aimed at students who are between 14 and 16 years of age.\r\n\r\n<strong>My daughter is home-schooled. If she follows the course, how do I go about getting her entered for the exam?</strong>\r\n\r\nHome-schooled students often miss out on the practical aspects of science courses. One of the great things about the international GCSE specification is that the assessment of experimental skills is through the examination paper – there is no practical exam or controlled assessment.\r\n\r\nAll you have to do is approach your local examination centre – which would normally be your closest secondary school – and ask their examinations officer if they can enter your daughter as an external candidate.\r\n\r\n<strong>My son is studying for his GCSE exams in Science, but he is following a different specification. Are these videos of any use to him?</strong>\r\n\r\nAbsolutely! The basic content is the same no matter what specification is being followed. The facts about photosynthesis are the same wherever you are in the world! I have produced an index for the videos on a pdf document, so it makes it really easy for your son to find the video that is most relevant to his requirements.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://igcsesciencecourses.com/contact-us/\"><span style=\"color: #0066cc;\">Contact Me</span></a> directly if you want to find out more about this.','Frequently Asked Questions','','inherit','closed','closed','','324-revision-v1','','','2015-12-16 17:37:47','2015-12-16 17:37:47','','324','http://pwd.igcsesciencecourses.com/324-revision-v1/','0','revision','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('498','1','2015-12-16 17:39:15','2015-12-16 17:39:15','<h2>iGCSE Science Courses</h2>\r\nOn my site you will find complete international GCSE science courses recorded on video from beginning to end. There are no other videos like these on the market!\r\n\r\nAs a teacher and tutor I had searched in vain to find suitable science video material that I could give to my students to watch between lessons or tutorials. No material was available so I therefore decided to create my own videos, and eighteen months later I have completed the Biology, Chemistry and Physics video courses.\r\n\r\nThese videos are invaluable support, irrespective of whether you are at school, college, or a mature student. You may be homeschooled, in which case my courses are ideal. You may be following a different course completely, but it doesn’t matter as the content is common to whatever specification you use.\r\n\r\nEach video consists of a presentation with my narration recorded over the top - it’s just like having me standing right next to you as your own personal teacher!\r\n\r\nHave a look at the sample videos on the Biology, Chemistry and Physics pages. I really do hope that you enjoy watching these videos as much as I have enjoyed making them!\r\n<h2>Graham Bray</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://igcsesciencecourses.com/images/graham.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nHi, I\'m Graham Bray and welcome to my iGCSE Science Courses website.\r\n\r\nI\'ve been a teacher for over 25 years, and am currently the Director of STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering and Maths) at a large comprehensive school in East Sussex. To bore you with the qualifications, I have a Joint Honours Degree in Botany and Zoology, and a PhD in Biological Sciences.  I was also one of the first Advanced Skills Teachers in Kent.\r\n\r\nI am a passionate believer in life-long learning, and I will do whatever I can to encourage learning for all ages.  Using videos to enhance learning has great potential, and I hope to exploit this potential via my website.\r\n\r\nOn a personal level I am married to a primary school headteacher, and we have two grown up daughters. We also have a little dog called Maisie-Rae! When not creating videos or teaching I relax (!) by working out at the gym, watching rugby and football, and doing a little work around the garden. I am also an avid fan of Grand Designs and The Apprentice.','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','322-revision-v1','','','2015-12-16 17:39:15','2015-12-16 17:39:15','','322','http://pwd.igcsesciencecourses.com/322-revision-v1/','0','revision','','0');
